The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Cash awards for MSCA youngsters

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The Mainland Sambaran Cricket Academy (MSCA) youngsters, who emerged champions in the CAB Ambar Roy sub-junior meet recently, were felicitated by Anjan Chatterjee, director, Mainland China chain of restaurants on Wednesday. Besides being presented with kits, they also received rich cash awards for their performances. 

While each player was given Rs 5,000, Man of the Tournament Subhajit Banerjee received Rs 11,000, promising all-rounder Swagatam Sur and promising off-spinner Asif Pradhan received Rs 7,500 each. 

MSCA is trying to rope in one among Gundappa Viswanath, Mohinder Amarnath and Dilip Vengsarkar as batting consultant. 

The sponsors have already decided to adopt Subhajit and are also considering an overseas exposure for him. 




